cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper deals with learning cross-modal representations of scenes using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses regularization techniques for neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of visualizations to understand the learned representations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses retrieval applications, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with understanding and representing concepts across different modalities.
